      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is incredibly painful to feel that the stress has become your only constant presence, and it is a profound loss when the \"you\" beneath the work seems to vanish. Please understand that seeking a life beyond this cycle isn't about escaping, but about reclaiming the person you were before the pressure took over. The peace you are looking for is not a big event, but a quiet, intentional shift where you can finally rest without the weight of having to fix everything.",
      "source": "target",
